On October 28, 2013, President Barack Obama issued a proclamation to honor the memory of Thomas S. Foley, former Speaker of the House of Representatives, who had passed away. The proclamation ordered that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at the White House, public buildings and grounds, military posts and naval stations, as well as on all naval vessels of the Federal Government in the District of Columbia, throughout the United States, and its territories and possessions on October 29, 2013. The flag was also to be flown at half-staff at all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations.